ily, as well as unpublished correspondence and drafts of poems, Kersnowski argues that Graves actually experienced the White Goddess as a real being and that his life as a poet was driven by the purpose of celebrating and explaining this deity and her matriarchy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAuthors, Englishy20th centuryvBiography. 0aModernism (Literature)zGreat Britain. 0aSoldierszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aWar neurosesxPatientsvBiography. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xVeteransvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/74343440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796393423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796393/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK